---
import Legal from '../layouts/Legal.astro';
import { COMPANY } from '../data/company';
---

<Legal
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description={`How ${COMPANY.legalName} collects, uses and protects personal data.`}
  path="/privacy"
  updated="8 June 2026"
>
  <p>
    This policy explains how <strong>{COMPANY.legalName}</strong> ("Aethon Labs", "we", "us")
    handles personal data collected through this website, <strong>{COMPANY.domain}</strong>. We
    are committed to protecting your privacy and processing data in line with the UK GDPR and the
    Data Protection Act 2018.
  </p>
  <p>
    This policy covers our corporate website only. Our products (such as Clinvara) operate under
    their own, separate privacy notices.
  </p>

  <h2>Who we are</h2>
  <p>
    {COMPANY.legalName} is a {COMPANY.companyType.toLowerCase()} registered in {
      COMPANY.jurisdiction
    } (company number {COMPANY.companyNumber}), with its registered office at {
      COMPANY.registeredOfficeOneLine
    }. For any data protection queries, contact us at <a href={`mailto:${COMPANY.email}`}
      >{COMPANY.email}</a
    >.
  </p>

  <h2>What we collect</h2>
  <p>This website is intentionally minimal. We may process:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Contact details you choose to share</strong> — if you email us, we receive your
      email address and the contents of your message.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Technical data</strong> — limited information your browser sends automatically (such
      as IP address and user agent) and any privacy-respecting analytics our hosting provider
      collects to keep the site secure and reliable.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do not sell personal data, and we do not use it for advertising.</p>

  <h2>Why we use it (lawful basis)</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To respond to your enquiries — our legitimate interest in communicating with you.</li>
    <li>To keep the website secure and operational — our legitimate interest in security.</li>
    <li>To meet legal and regulatory obligations where they apply.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
  <p>
    We retain correspondence only as long as needed to handle your enquiry and for a reasonable
    period afterwards, then delete it. Technical logs are kept for a short period for security and
    diagnostics.
  </p>

  <h2>Sharing</h2>
  <p>
    We use trusted service providers (for example, our website host and email provider) who
    process data on our behalf under appropriate agreements. We may disclose data where required
    by law. We do not otherwise share your personal data with third parties.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Under UK data protection law you have rights to access, rectify, erase, restrict and object to
    the processing of your personal data, and to data portability. To exercise any of these,
    email <a href={`mailto:${COMPANY.email}`}>{COMPANY.email}</a>. You also have the right to
    complain to the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) at <a
      href="https://ico.org.uk"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a
    >.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy from time to time. The "last updated" date above reflects the most
    recent revision.
  </p>

  <p>
    <em
      >This notice is provided for transparency and does not constitute legal advice. It will be
      reviewed as our products and processing activities develop.</em
    >
  </p>
</Legal>
